<HL>
   International Brief -- Rheinmetall Berlin AG:
   Company Says Pretax Profit
   Grew 13% in the First Half
</HL>
<DATE>
08/15/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   G.RHM
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Rheinmetall Berlin AG said its group pretax profit rose
13% in the first half of 1990 to 117.4 million German marks
($74.4 million) from 104.4 million marks a year earlier.
   The big West German maker of weapons, machinery and
automotive electronics said its financial results in the
first half were better than expected.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Looking ahead for the remainder of 1990, the company said
it expects "satisfactory developments for sales and earnings"
for the world-wide group.
</TEXT>
